The Tritart watercolor set makes your pictures unique and professional  There is a little artist in each of us  as soon as we dip the brush into the color palette and the first strokes appear on the white paper   The watercolor technique is a very special type of painting in which the transparency of the colors is in the foreground  The more water is added to the colors  the more transparent the color layer becomes  In order to still retain good color depth and luminosity  we have used a high quality process to achieve a particularly high level of color pigmentation  which gives your images that certain something   Especially with the glazing technique  transparency and simultaneous color brilliance are extremely important  because with this technique a transparent layer is applied over an already dry layer of paint  so that the lower layer can still be seen  With our artist watercolor paint set you are guaranteed to succeed in this technique   Another technique is the wet on wet technique  for example for clouds and areas that require a washed out look  Our high quality Tritart artist watercolor paints are also very suitable for this  because in contrast to cheap paints from the Far East  high quality watercolor paints are more extensive and brighter   The watercolor color set at a glance    40 watercolor paints   10 sheets of watercolor pad   1 wooden brush   1 Water Brush Pen   1 watercolor sponge   1 gift box   storage box  Tip   In our shop you will find other painting accessories  such as fine brushes  water brush pens in different thicknesses  brush cleaners and watercolor paper different sizes and colors  Tritart offers you everything you need to do with creative design

Ingenious crafting fun with the shrink film craft set for young and old With shrink film there are hardly any limits to your creativity  The great properties of the film are ideal for crafting   no matter what you feel like  Why not just buy shrink film and try it out  What is shrink film anyway  The shrinking plastic film is a transparent film that opens after a short warm up in the oven slightly less than half of the original size shrinks  First it curls and bends  then it sinks again and remains wonderfully smooth  Shrinking not only makes the shrink plastic smaller  but also strengthens it and makes it more stable  How is the film used  The films have a smooth and a roughened side  The rough side is actually better for painting because the paint sticks better and therefore covers better  Of course  if you want  you can also paint on the smooth side  After painting  the shrink film simply needs to be cut to size and heated in the oven for 1 2 minutes  Then just take it out  let it cool down and the work of art is ready   Craft tips with shrink plastic   Pay attention to the size  as the film shrinks by approx  50    In principle  any type of pen works  but felt tip pens are particularly suitable for a bright  vibrant result   On the rough side the colors become richer  more even  _  _ig   Which side should be facing down in the oven  In principle it doesn t matter  but we recommend placing the smooth side down for an optimally smooth result You can find these and other products in our craft online shop  Be inspired and browse through our extensive range  You are guaranteed to find more ideas for new craft projects
